Multiple FPGAs on a Board
text:
(ref: https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=33032036)

I'm looking for multiple FPGAs on a single board. The prior request got only a single response, the HTG-847 ( https://www.xilinx.com/products/boards-and-kits/1-fb2a7b.html ). However, the board is too expensive and could not be programmed by open source software.

The ideal case is a single board with 4 chips (and a scalable design to other powers of 2).

The goal is a board to experiment with various software / hardware architectures that is fully programmable.

The only solution seems to be to create such a board. At the moment I'm looking the Artix 7 100T chip (https://docs.xilinx.com/v/u/en-US/ds181_Artix_7_Data_Sheet). It can be programmed with open source software.

Suggestions, comments, and snide remarks are most welcome.
